Usage:  design-ai install [--json]

Symlinks design-ai skills, slash commands, and agents into Claude Code.
Uses CLAUDE_HOME and DESIGN_AI_PREFIX when provided.

Options:
  --json                         Emit machine-readable install result

Environment:
  CLAUDE_HOME=/path/to/.claude    Target Claude Code home directory
  DESIGN_AI_PREFIX=mydesign-     Prefix for installed skill and command names
Usage:  design-ai update [--dry-run] [--json]

Pulls the latest git source when DESIGN_AI_HOME is a clone, then re-runs install.sh.
For npm installs, update the package with npm and then run install again.

Options:
  --dry-run                      Preview git/install actions without changing files
  --json                         Emit machine-readable dry-run plan; requires --dry-run

Environment:
  DESIGN_AI_HOME=/path/to/source  Source repository or package root
  CLAUDE_HOME=/path/to/.claude    Target Claude Code home directory
  DESIGN_AI_PREFIX=mydesign-     Prefix for installed skill and command names
Usage:  design-ai uninstall [--json]

Removes design-ai symlinks from Claude Code while keeping the source files.
Uses CLAUDE_HOME and DESIGN_AI_PREFIX to find the installed links.

Options:
  --json                         Emit machine-readable uninstall result

Environment:
  CLAUDE_HOME=/path/to/.claude    Target Claude Code home directory
  DESIGN_AI_PREFIX=mydesign-     Prefix for installed skill and command names
Usage:  design-ai status [--json]

Shows design-ai symlinks currently installed in Claude Code.
Set VERBOSE=1 to print each installed skill, command, and agent name.

Options:
  --json                         Emit machine-readable install status

Environment:
  CLAUDE_HOME=/path/to/.claude    Target Claude Code home directory
  DESIGN_AI_HOME=/path/to/source  Source repository or package root
  DESIGN_AI_PREFIX=mydesign-     Prefix for installed skill and command names
  VERBOSE=1                       Print full installed item lists
Usage:  design-ai list [skills|commands|agents] [--json]

Lists catalog entries from the plugin manifest.
Omit the kind to print all catalog sections.

Arguments:
  skills     List installed skill playbooks
  commands   List slash command templates
  agents     List bundled agent personas

Options:
  --json     Emit machine-readable catalog entries
Usage:  design-ai search <query> [--limit N] [--dir kind] [--json]

Searches markdown files across knowledge, examples, skills, docs, agents, and commands.

Options:
  --limit N   Maximum hits to return, 1-500. Default: 20
  --dir kind  Restrict to one corpus directory. Repeatable.
              kind: knowledge, examples, skills, docs, agents, commands
  --json      Emit machine-readable results
Usage:  design-ai show <file[:line|start-end]> [--lines N:M] [--context N] [--json]

Prints a file from DESIGN_AI_HOME. Search results like `knowledge/foo.md:42` are accepted.

Options:
  --lines N:M   Print an exact line range. Also accepts N-M.
  --context N   Context lines around a single `file:line`. Default: 8
  --json        Emit machine-readable output
