        cat brief.md | design-ai route --stdin [--limit N] [--explain] [--json]

Recommends the best design-ai command, skill, and knowledge files for a task brief.
Route eval is read-only and checks deterministic agent routing fixtures.

Options:
  --from-file file  Read the task brief, or route eval JSON with --eval, from a file
  --stdin           Read the task brief, or route eval JSON with --eval, from standard input
  --list            List route ids without scoring a brief
  --limit N         Maximum route recommendations to return, 1-10. Default: 3
  --explain         Include route scoring and reference coverage details
  --eval-template   Generate a runnable route eval checkpoint JSON template
  --eval            Run deterministic route-selection checkpoint cases
  --strict          With --eval, exit non-zero on warning or failure
  --json            Emit machine-readable route results

Examples:
  design-ai route "audit a Figma signup flow for Korean fintech"
  design-ai route "spec a Button component" --explain
  design-ai route --list
  design-ai route --eval-template --json > route-eval.json
  design-ai route --eval --from-file route-eval.json --strict --json
  design-ai route --from-file product-brief.md
  design-ai route "spec a Button component" --json
Usage:  design-ai routes [--json]

Lists route ids that can be passed to prompt, pack, examples, and check.
Equivalent to: design-ai route --list

Options:
  --json   Emit machine-readable route catalog
Usage:  design-ai prompt <brief> [--route id] [--with-learning] [--learning-category kind] [--learning-limit N] [--json] [--out file] [--force]
        design-ai prompt --from-file brief.md [--route id] [--with-learning] [--learning-category kind] [--learning-limit N] [--json] [--out file] [--force]
        design-ai prompt --eval-template [--json] [--out file] [--force]
        design-ai prompt --eval --from-file prompt-eval.json [--strict] [--json] [--out file] [--force]
        cat prompt-eval.json | design-ai prompt --eval --stdin [--strict] [--json]
        cat brief.md | design-ai prompt --stdin [--route id] [--with-learning] [--learning-category kind] [--learning-limit N] [--json]

Builds a ready-to-use prompt from route recommendations and required design-ai files.
Prompt eval is read-only and checks generated prompt-plan contracts.

Options:
  --from-file file  Read the task brief, or prompt eval JSON with --eval, from a file
  --stdin           Read the task brief, or prompt eval JSON with --eval, from standard input
  --route id        Force a route id from `design-ai route --json`
  --with-learning   Include brief-relevant local learning preferences and record local usage metadata
  --learning-category kind  Include only one learning category; requires --with-learning
  --learning-limit N        Limit included learning entries, 1-100; requires --with-learning
  --eval-template   Generate a runnable prompt eval checkpoint JSON template
  --eval            Run deterministic prompt-plan checkpoint cases
  --strict          With --eval, exit non-zero on warning or failure
  --json            Emit machine-readable prompt plan
  --out file        Write output to a file instead of stdout
  --force           Overwrite an existing --out file

Environment:
  DESIGN_AI_LEARNING_FILE=/path/learning.json        Override the profile used by --with-learning
  DESIGN_AI_LEARNING_USAGE_FILE=/path/usage.json     Override the local usage sidecar path

Examples:
  design-ai prompt "audit a Figma signup flow for Korean fintech"
  design-ai prompt "audit checkout UX" --with-learning --learning-category korean --learning-limit 5
  design-ai prompt --from-file product-brief.md --route design-review --out prompt.md
  design-ai prompt "spec a Button component API" --json --out button-prompt.json
  design-ai prompt --eval-template --json > prompt-eval.json
  design-ai prompt --eval --from-file prompt-eval.json --strict --json
