        design-ai check --examples --all-routes [--limit N] [--issues-only] [--strict] [--json]

Checks generated design-ai Markdown artifacts for grounding, accessibility, responsive, unresolved-marker, and route-specific requirements.

Options:
  --stdin     Read artifact Markdown from standard input
  --examples  Check worked examples for the selected route
  --all-routes  Check worked examples for every route
  --route id  Add route-specific checks such as component-spec, palette-from-brand, or slide-deck
  --limit N   Number of route examples to check, 1-25. Default: 3
  --issues-only  In human output, show only warnings and failures
  --strict    Treat warnings as a failing exit code
  --learn     Capture warning/failure checks as local learning entries
  --yes       Apply --learn entries instead of previewing them
  --learning-file path  Override the learning profile used by --learn
  --json      Emit machine-readable check results
