Stores local design preferences for explicit prompt personalization.
This is local memory, not model training or fine-tuning.

Options:
  --init               Preview or apply starter local learning entries for dogfood use
  --remember text      Remember an inline preference or project constraint
  --feedback text      Convert outcome feedback into a reusable local learning note
  --outcome kind       Feedback outcome: keep, improve, avoid. Default: improve
  --from-file file     Read remember/feedback text or import/verify/diff/restore/redact JSON from a file
  --stdin              Read remember/feedback text or import/verify/diff/restore/redact JSON from standard input
  --category kind      preference, brand, workflow, constraint, accessibility, korean, other
  --query text         Filter list/export output to entries whose category or text matches the query
  --explain            With --list, include selection score, matched tokens, and reason
  --limit N            Limit list/export output to the N most recent matching entries, 1-100
  --list               List saved learning entries. Default when no action is given
  --export             Print the learned-context block used by --with-learning
  --backup             Print a full portable learning-profile backup; use --json for importable JSON
  --redact             Print a portable JSON backup with sensitive-looking text redacted
  --verify             Validate a portable learning JSON payload without importing it
  --diff               Compare the active profile against a portable learning JSON payload without importing it
  --restore            Preview or apply replacing the active profile with a portable learning JSON payload
  --restore-backups    List sibling restore rollback backups for the active learning profile
  --prune              With --restore-backups, preview or delete older rollback backup files
  --keep N             With --restore-backups --prune, keep the N newest backups. Default: 5
  --backup-file path   With --restore, override the automatic rollback backup file path
  --import             Merge entries from a JSON learning profile or learn --export --json payload
  --audit              Inspect profile shape, sensitive content, and cleanup suggestions without changing it
  --fix                With --audit, prepare or apply safe cleanup suggestions
  --curate             Preview or apply archive-first curation for duplicate/sensitive entries, plus usage review hints
  --report             With --curate, --signals, --agent-backlog, or --propose-skills, emit a Markdown review report instead of human console output
  --patch              With --propose-skills, emit a preview-only unified diff handoff without editing skill files
  --review-check       With --propose-skills, verify the review file against current proposals without changing files
  --apply-plan         With --propose-skills, turn accepted review decisions into a read-only manual apply plan
  --review-template    With --propose-skills, emit a JSON proposal review-file template without changing review decisions
  --dry-run            Preview --init, --import, --restore, --curate, --restore-backups --prune, or --audit --fix without changing files
  --stats              Summarize profile counts, recency, and audit status without changing it
  --usage              Summarize prompt/pack --with-learning usage sidecar events without changing files
  --signals            Summarize local learning, usage, eval, check-capture, agent backlog, and workspace readiness signals without changing files
  --agent-backlog      Emit a focused local AI/agent development backlog from the signal registry without changing files
  --propose-skills     Preview skill instruction deltas from repeated check-capture learning signals without changing files
  --min-evidence N     With --propose-skills, require N related check-capture entries before emitting a proposal. Default: 2
  --review-file path   With --propose-skills, read proposal review decisions without changing the review file
  --eval-template      Generate a runnable learning eval checkpoint from the active profile
  --eval               Run deterministic learning-selection checkpoint cases without changing files
  --strict             With --eval, --signals, --agent-backlog, or --propose-skills, exit non-zero when any checkpoint, signal, backlog, or proposal gate warns or fails
  --forget id-or-number Remove one entry by id or 1-based list number; requires --yes
  --clear              Remove all saved learning entries; requires --yes
  --yes                Confirm destructive local profile changes
  --file path          Override the learning profile path
  --usage-file path    Override the learning usage sidecar path used by --usage, --curate, --signals, --agent-backlog, or --propose-skills
  --json               Emit machine-readable output
  --out file           Write JSON output to a file, export Markdown for --export, or learning review report Markdown
  --force              Overwrite an existing --out file, or an existing --backup-file during --restore

Environment:
  DESIGN_AI_LEARNING_FILE=/path/learning.json       Override the default profile path
  DESIGN_AI_LEARNING_USAGE_FILE=/path/usage.json    Override the default usage sidecar path

Examples:
  design-ai learn --init
  design-ai learn --init --yes --json
  design-ai learn --remember "Prefer dense Korean product UI" --category korean
  design-ai learn --feedback "Keep audit findings short and evidence-led" --outcome keep
  design-ai learn --feedback --from-file feedback.md --outcome improve
  cat feedback.md | design-ai learn --feedback --stdin --outcome avoid --category brand
  design-ai learn --list --category korean --limit 5
  design-ai learn --list --query "keyboard accessibility" --explain --json
  design-ai learn --export --query "pricing page" --limit 3
  design-ai learn --backup --json --out learning-backup.json
  design-ai learn --redact --json --out learning-redacted.json
  design-ai learn --redact --from-file learning-backup.json --json --out learning-redacted.json --force
  design-ai learn --verify --from-file learning-backup.json
  design-ai learn --diff --from-file learning-backup.json --json
  design-ai learn --restore --from-file learning-backup.json --dry-run
  design-ai learn --restore --from-file learning-backup.json --yes --backup-file learning-before-restore.json
  design-ai learn --restore-backups --json
  design-ai learn --restore-backups --prune --keep 5
  design-ai learn --restore-backups --prune --keep 5 --yes
  design-ai learn --import --from-file learning.json --dry-run
  design-ai learn --audit
  design-ai learn --audit --fix --dry-run
  design-ai learn --curate
  design-ai learn --curate --usage-file ./learning.usage.json
  design-ai learn --curate --report --out learning-curation-report.md
  design-ai learn --curate --yes --json
  design-ai learn --stats --json
  design-ai learn --usage --json
  design-ai learn --signals --from-file . --json
  design-ai learn --signals --from-file . --report --out learning-signals.md
  design-ai learn --agent-backlog --from-file . --report --out agent-backlog.md
  design-ai learn --propose-skills --from-file . --min-evidence 3 --json
  design-ai learn --propose-skills --from-file . --strict --json
  design-ai learn --propose-skills --from-file . --review-file skill-proposals.review.json --strict --json
  design-ai learn --propose-skills --from-file . --review-file skill-proposals.review.json --review-check --json
  design-ai learn --propose-skills --from-file . --review-file skill-proposals.review.json --apply-plan --json
  design-ai learn --propose-skills --from-file . --review-template --out skill-proposals.review.json
  design-ai learn --propose-skills --from-file . --report --out skill-proposals.md
  design-ai learn --propose-skills --from-file . --patch --out skill-proposals.patch
  design-ai learn --eval-template --query "keyboard accessibility" --out learning-eval.json
  design-ai learn --eval --from-file learning-eval.json --strict --json
  design-ai learn --forget learn-abc123def0 --yes
  design-ai prompt "audit checkout UX" --with-learning
  design-ai pack "spec a pricing page" --with-learning
Usage:  design-ai workspace [--root path] [--learning-file path] [--learning-usage path] [--learning-eval path] [--strict] [--json]

Shows the current local dogfood workspace state without changing files.

Options:
  --root path           Inspect a specific git workspace root. Default: current directory
  --learning-file path  Inspect a specific learning profile. Default: DESIGN_AI_LEARNING_FILE or ~/.design-ai/learning.json
  --learning-usage path Include a read-only local learning usage sidecar summary. Default: auto-detect sibling learning.usage.json
  --learning-eval path  Include a read-only local learning eval checkpoint summary. Default: auto-detect sibling learning-eval.json
  --strict              Exit non-zero when readiness warnings or failures are present
  --json                Emit machine-readable workspace diagnostics
