        design-ai site <workspace.json> --prompt template-id [--task id-or-number] [--out file] [--force]

Validates Website Improvement Console JSON exports and turns them into local handoff artifacts.

Options:
  --stdin     Read workspace JSON from standard input
  --init      Generate a real-project Website Improvement workspace JSON from CLI fields
  --name text Site name for --init
  --live-url url
              Live website URL for --init
  --repo-url url
              Target website repository URL for --init; this repo is not mutated
  --local-path path
              Target website local path for --init; this repo is not mutated
  --figma-url url
              Figma reference URL for --init
  --brand-notes text
              Design system, brand, voice, or constraint notes for --init
  --deploy provider
              Deployment provider for --init: vercel, netlify, cloudflare, other, none
  --sentry project
              Sentry project reference for --init
  --cms kind  CMS for --init: sanity, contentful, wordpress, shopify, none, other
  --database kind
              Database for --init: supabase, neon, postgres, none, other
  --page path Add a priority page for --init; repeatable
  --flow text Add a key user flow for --init; repeatable
  --viewport kind
              Add a viewport for --init: desktop, tablet, mobile; repeatable
  --from-intake file|--stdin
              Generate a workspace, task-ready workspace, next-actions report, or handoff bundle from a filled intake Markdown file or stdin
  --intake-template
              Emit a blank company website intake Markdown template before --init or --bundle
  --language code
              With --intake-template, emit en or ko template content; default: en
  --sample    Emit a valid sample Website Improvement workspace JSON
  --prompt-list
              List Website Improvement prompt template ids and intended use
  --mcp-check
              Check MCP readiness evidence and task/MCP gaps without external MCP calls
  --probes
              Add read-only local URL/path/tool-handoff probes to --mcp-check or --mcp-plan; no external writes or MCP calls
  --mcp-plan
              Generate a Markdown or JSON MCP readiness action plan without external MCP calls
  --next-actions
              Generate a prioritized local next-action list from validation, MCP readiness, and refactor tasks; can be combined with --init
  --graph
              Export a portable Website Improvement workflow graph without external MCP calls
  --tasks     Emit workspace JSON with starter refactor tasks generated from audit findings
  --bundle    Write a complete local handoff bundle directory; can be combined with --init
  --bundle-check
              Validate a generated handoff bundle directory, including SHA-256 checksums
  --bundle-compare dir
              Compare two generated handoff bundles by bundle digest, checksums, and summary metadata
  --bundle-handoff
              Generate a target-repo Codex handoff prompt from a validated handoff bundle
  --bundle-repair
              Preview or apply local handoff bundle regeneration from embedded website-workspace.tasks.json
  --yes       With --bundle-repair, rewrite the handoff bundle directory and re-run bundle-check
  --strict    Exit non-zero when validation warnings or failures are present
  --json      Emit a machine-readable validation summary
  --report    Generate a Markdown website improvement handoff report
  --prompts   Generate a Markdown bundle of Codex and Claude prompts
  --prompt id Generate one Markdown prompt template
              id: codex-repo-intake, codex-implementation, codex-visual-qa, codex-deployment, claude-design-review, claude-competitor, claude-copy-ux, handoff-report
  --task id   Select a refactor task by id or 1-based top-task number; requires --prompt codex-implementation or --bundle-handoff
  --out file  Write --json, --init, --intake-template, --sample, --prompt-list, --mcp-check, --mcp-plan, --next-actions, --graph, --tasks, --bundle, --bundle-check, --bundle-compare, --bundle-handoff, --bundle-repair, --report, --prompts, or --prompt output to a file or directory
  --force     Overwrite an existing --out file

Examples:
  design-ai site --init --name "Company marketing site" --live-url https://example.com --repo-url https://github.com/acme/site --page / --page /pricing --flow "Visitor compares plans and starts signup" --out website-workspace.json
  design-ai site --init --name "Company marketing site" --live-url https://example.com --repo-url https://github.com/acme/site --next-actions --out website-next-actions.md
  design-ai site --init --name "Company marketing site" --live-url https://example.com --repo-url https://github.com/acme/site --bundle --out website-handoff-bundle
  design-ai site --from-intake company-website-intake.ko.md --out website-workspace.json
  cat company-website-intake.ko.md | design-ai site --from-intake --stdin --json
  cat company-website-intake.ko.md | design-ai site --from-intake --stdin --out website-workspace.json --force
  design-ai site --from-intake company-website-intake.ko.md --next-actions --out website-next-actions.md
  cat company-website-intake.ko.md | design-ai site --from-intake --stdin --next-actions --out website-next-actions.md --force
  design-ai site --from-intake company-website-intake.ko.md --tasks --out website-workspace.tasks.json
  cat company-website-intake.ko.md | design-ai site --from-intake --stdin --tasks --out website-workspace.tasks.json --force
  design-ai site --from-intake company-website-intake.ko.md --bundle --tasks --out website-handoff-bundle
  cat company-website-intake.ko.md | design-ai site --from-intake --stdin --bundle --tasks --out website-handoff-bundle
  design-ai site --intake-template --out company-website-intake.md
  design-ai site --intake-template --language ko --out company-website-intake.ko.md
  design-ai site --sample --out website-workspace.json
  design-ai site --prompt-list --json
  design-ai site website-workspace.json --mcp-check --json
  design-ai site website-workspace.json --mcp-check --probes --json
  design-ai site website-workspace.json --mcp-check --probes --json --out mcp-check-probes.json
  design-ai site website-workspace.json --mcp-plan --out mcp-action-plan.md
  design-ai site website-workspace.json --mcp-plan --probes --json
  design-ai site website-workspace.json --mcp-plan --probes --json --out mcp-action-plan-probes.json
  design-ai site website-workspace.json --next-actions --json
  design-ai site website-workspace.json --next-actions --out website-next-actions.md
  design-ai site website-workspace.json --graph --json --out website-workflow-graph.json
  design-ai site website-workspace.json --tasks --out website-workspace.tasks.json
  design-ai site website-workspace.json --bundle --out website-handoff-bundle
  design-ai site website-handoff-bundle --bundle-check --json
  design-ai site website-handoff-bundle --bundle-compare website-handoff-bundle.previous --json
  design-ai site website-handoff-bundle --bundle-handoff --out target-repo-prompt.md
  design-ai site website-handoff-bundle --bundle-handoff --task task-accessibility --out target-repo-task-prompt.md
  design-ai site website-handoff-bundle --bundle-repair --json
  design-ai site website-handoff-bundle --bundle-repair --json --out bundle-repair-preview.json
  design-ai site website-handoff-bundle --bundle-repair --yes --json
  design-ai site website-workspace.json --json
