  design-ai site website-workspace.json --prompt codex-implementation --task task-accessibility --out task-accessibility.md
Usage:  design-ai mcp

Starts the design-ai stdio MCP server for Claude Code, Codex, and other MCP clients.
The server writes only JSON-RPC messages to stdout; diagnostics go to stderr.

Examples:
  Claude Code:
  claude mcp add --transport stdio design-ai -- design-ai mcp
  Codex:
  codex mcp add design-ai -- design-ai mcp
  Local clone:
  node cli/bin/design-ai-mcp.mjs
Usage:  design-ai version [--json]

Prints the CLI package version, plugin/corpus version, and source root.

Options:
  --json   Emit machine-readable version metadata
Usage:  design-ai help [command]
        design-ai help --json

Shows top-level CLI help, or command-specific help when a command is provided.

Options:
  --json  Emit machine-readable help topic catalog

Examples:
  design-ai help
  design-ai help --json
  design-ai help route
  design-ai help prompt
  design-ai help doctor
Usage:  design-ai install [--json]

Symlinks design-ai skills, slash commands, and agents into Claude Code.
Uses CLAUDE_HOME and DESIGN_AI_PREFIX when provided.

Options:
  --json                         Emit machine-readable install result

Environment:
  CLAUDE_HOME=/path/to/.claude    Target Claude Code home directory
  DESIGN_AI_PREFIX=mydesign-     Prefix for installed skill and command names
Usage:  design-ai update [--dry-run] [--json]

Pulls the latest git source when DESIGN_AI_HOME is a clone, then re-runs install.sh.
For npm installs, update the package with npm and then run install again.

Options:
  --dry-run                      Preview git/install actions without changing files
  --json                         Emit machine-readable dry-run plan; requires --dry-run

Environment:
  DESIGN_AI_HOME=/path/to/source  Source repository or package root
  CLAUDE_HOME=/path/to/.claude    Target Claude Code home directory
  DESIGN_AI_PREFIX=mydesign-     Prefix for installed skill and command names
