Usage:  design-ai route <brief> [--limit N] [--explain] [--json]
        design-ai route --from-file brief.md [--limit N] [--explain] [--json]
        design-ai route --list [--json]
        design-ai route --eval-template [--json]
        design-ai route --eval --from-file route-eval.json [--strict] [--json]
        cat route-eval.json | design-ai route --eval --stdin [--strict] [--json]
        cat brief.md | design-ai route --stdin [--limit N] [--explain] [--json]

Recommends the best design-ai command, skill, and knowledge files for a task brief.
Route eval is read-only and checks deterministic agent routing fixtures.

Options:
  --from-file file  Read the task brief, or route eval JSON with --eval, from a file
  --stdin           Read the task brief, or route eval JSON with --eval, from standard input
  --list            List route ids without scoring a brief
  --limit N         Maximum route recommendations to return, 1-10. Default: 3
  --explain         Include route scoring and reference coverage details
  --eval-template   Generate a runnable route eval checkpoint JSON template
  --eval            Run deterministic route-selection checkpoint cases
  --strict          With --eval, exit non-zero on warning or failure
  --json            Emit machine-readable route results

Examples:
  design-ai route "audit a Figma signup flow for Korean fintech"
  design-ai route "spec a Button component" --explain
  design-ai route --list
  design-ai route --eval-template --json > route-eval.json
  design-ai route --eval --from-file route-eval.json --strict --json
  design-ai route --from-file product-brief.md
  design-ai route "spec a Button component" --json
Usage:  design-ai check <artifact.md> [--strict] [--json] [--route id] [--learn [--yes] [--learning-file path]]
        cat artifact.md | design-ai check --stdin [--strict] [--route id] [--learn [--yes] [--learning-file path]]
        design-ai check --examples --route id [--limit N] [--issues-only] [--strict] [--json]
        design-ai check --examples --all-routes [--limit N] [--issues-only] [--strict] [--json]

Checks generated design-ai Markdown artifacts for grounding, accessibility, responsive, unresolved-marker, and route-specific requirements.

Options:
  --stdin     Read artifact Markdown from standard input
  --examples  Check worked examples for the selected route
  --all-routes  Check worked examples for every route
  --route id  Add route-specific checks such as component-spec, palette-from-brand, or slide-deck
  --limit N   Number of route examples to check, 1-25. Default: 3
  --issues-only  In human output, show only warnings and failures
  --strict    Treat warnings as a failing exit code
  --learn     Capture warning/failure checks as local learning entries
  --yes       Apply --learn entries instead of previewing them
  --learning-file path  Override the learning profile used by --learn
  --json      Emit machine-readable check results
Usage:  design-ai audit [--strict] [--quiet] [--json]

Runs the same 8 repository audits used by CI:
  frontmatter, link, Korean copy, raw hex, integration, stale, coverage, example QA

Options:
  --strict   Exit non-zero when any supported audit fails
  --quiet    Print only failures and the final summary
  --json     Emit machine-readable audit results
Usage:  design-ai doctor [--strict] [--json] [--fix]

Checks source layout, versions, runtimes, audit tooling, and Claude Code symlinks.

Options:
  --strict   Exit non-zero when warnings are present
  --json     Emit machine-readable diagnostics
  --fix      Re-run install.sh when diagnostics show only fixable warnings
